text: Sörby or Sørby may refer to: ==Places== * Sörby (Öland), a village in Sweden * Sörby, Västergötland, a former parish in Sweden for which Floby station was first named * Sørby, the administrative centre of Våle, a Norwegian village ==People== * Kari Sørby, a Norwegian television news anchor * Kristin Sørby, maiden name of Kristin Vinje * Mrs. Sørby, a character in the play The Wild Duck by the Norwegian playwright Henrik Ibsen ==Other== * Sörby IK, a Swedish football club; see Swedish Football Division 7 ==See also== * Sorby * Sarby * Sørbyhaugen (station)
title: Sörby
